article.headline: Texas Southern 98, Alabama A&amp,M 57
article.story: HOUSTON -- Travele Jones scored 21 points and had 10 rebounds as Texas Southern routed Alabama A&M 98-57 Monday night in its final home game of the season. Abdallah Boune added 19 points and Junior Treasure 16 for the Tigers (13-15, 9-7 Southwestern Athletic Conference), who led by 25 at halftime. Bo Amusa scored 12 points to lead the Bulldogs (10-14, 7-9), who hit only 16-of-52 field goals (30.8 percent). Texas Southern put together a 17-4 run late in the first half for a 40-16 advantage with 4:52 left before intermission and went into the break up 49-24. Alabama A&M opened the second half with a 20-6 run to pull to within 11 with 15:43 to play. The Tigers responded with a 15-2 run and led by at least 22 the rest of the game.
